Sweden) was used to perform multivariate analysis including 
principal component analysis (PCA) and orthogonal partial 
least square discriminant analysis (OPLS-DA). Permuta-
tion test was conducted to check whether the model was at 
the risk of over-fitting. We used Student’s t-test (SPSS 19.0 
software) to calculate the statistical significance. p value 
after the Benjamini–Hochberg false discovery rate (FDR) 
adjustment was less than 0.05 that was considered significant 
difference. Cluster analysis was performed using the online 
software MetaboAnalyst (http://​www.​metab​oanal​yst.​ca/). 
The diagnostic performance was assessed by area under the 
receiver-operating characteristic curve (ROC), which was 
usually used to evaluate overall discriminate ability.
Results
Experimental Design and Demographic Data
In order to use the data efficiently, we use random sampling 
method to divide the samples into train set and validation 
set. Firstly, the differential metabolites are obtained by mod-
eling analyzing the data in the train set, and then the diag-
nostic effect of the differential metabolites is evaluated in the 
validation set. The discovery and evaluation of differential 
metabolites are carried out in two relatively independent 
data sets, which can explain the accuracy and repeatability 
of the results to a certain extent.
GC–MS Analysis of Plasma Samples
In this study, GC–MS QP2010 (Shimadzu, Japan) and DB-5 
chromatographic column were used to separate and detect 
the pretreated plasma samples. The plasma of 62 patients 
with PD and 60 healthy controls were analyzed, and the 
metabolic components of plasma samples were well sepa-
rated (Fig. 1). In this study, 47 components were preliminar-
ily identified (Table 2), including amino acids, fatty acids, 
and carbohydrates.
Stability Evaluation
In order to evaluate the stability of the analytical method 
and the instrument, the mixture of plasma from health and 
PD was used as the quality control. Quality control runs 
through the whole injection process, about 9 samples per 
