Qualitative Identification of Potential Biomarkers
After multivariate statistical analysis and ROC analysis, 
we obtained three candidate compounds with the ability to 
diagnose PD. In order to verify the three potential markers 
obtained above, chemical standards were used for qualitative 
confirmation. The results showed that the qualitative data 
of acetic acid and propanoic acid in the sample were highly 
consistent with those of the standard. As the standard of 
2,3,4-trihydroxybutyric acid cannot be purchased, qualita-
tive identification of 2,3,4-trihydroxybutyric acid was not 
confirmed (Fig. 7).
Pathway Analysis of Potential Biomarkers
Pathway enrichment analysis was performed to explore 
changes in metabolic pathways with respect to Parkinson’s 
disease onset and progression. Based on the differential 
metabolites, 3 metabolic pathways were enriched (Fig. 8A). 
Pyruvate metabolism was the most significantly enriched 
pathway, followed by propanoate metabolism and glycolysis/
gluconeogenesis. Pyruvate is an intermediate product which 
plays a key role in glycometabolism. Pyruvate can realize 
the mutual transformation of glucose and fatty acids in vivo 
through acetyl CoA and tricarboxylic acid circulation. 
